Involuntary Shapechange			KEY:Drawback ~ Involuntary Shapechange					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback										PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassDrawbackRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Involuntary Shapechange]	PRERACE:1,Kitsune																				DESC:You are unable to maintain proper control over your shapeshifting abilities while impaired, causing features such as your ears, legs, tail, or tail to revert to their true form. While using change shape, you lose the +10 racial bonus on Disguise checks granted by change shape while you are sickened or nauseated. Additionally, each time you become sickened, nauseated, or suffer any amount of ability damage or ability drain while using change shape you must reroll your Disguise check and use the worse result. You cannot select this drawback if you possess the naturalize alternate racial trait.																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.28

